cs_block_tiktok_scripts_descr: The TikTok Pixel is a measurement tool that tracks TikTok ads' impact on the website. It enables marketers to monitor sales, user activity, and find the right audience for their ads.
cs_block_twitter_scripts_descr: The Twitter Pixel is a measurement tool that tracks Twitter ads' impact on the website. It enables marketers to monitor sales, user activity, and find the right audience for their ads.
cs_block_google_analytics_scripts_descr: Google Analytics lets you measure your advertising ROI as well as track your Flash, video, and social networking sites and applications
cs_block_google_ads_tag_scripts_descr: Google Ads (formerly Google AdWords)is an online advertising platform developed by Google, where advertisers bid to display brief advertisements, service offerings, product listings, or videos to web users.
cs_block_ad_storage_scripts_descr: Enables storage (such as cookies) related to advertising.
cs_block_analytics_storage_scripts_descr: Enables storage (such as cookies) related to analytics e.g. visit duration.
cs_block_ad_user_data_scripts_descr: Sets consent for sending user data related to advertising to Google.
cs_block_url_passthrough_scripts_descr: Passing information about Ad clicks, such as ad click, client ID, and session ID, through URL parameters.
cs_block_google_tag_manager_scripts_desc: Google Publisher Tag (GPT) is an ad tag library which allows publishers to define inventory, initiate and bundle ad requests, and render matching demand. GPT takes key details from you (such as ad unit code, ad size, and key-values), builds the request, and displays the ad on web pages.
cs_block_fb_pixel_scripts_descr: The Facebook pixel is a piece of code that collects data that helps to track conversions from Facebook ads, optimize ads, build targeted audiences for future ads and remarket to people who have already taken some kind of action on the website.
cs_block_tw_tag_scripts_descr: The Twitter Tag enables website owners to measure return on ad spend by tracking the actions people take after viewing or engaging with ads on Twitter.
cs_block_big_tag_scripts_descr: Microsoft UET (Universal Event Tracking) collects data about user interactions on your website to help measure performance and optimize advertising campaigns. It enables tracking for services like Microsoft Advertising (Bing Ads), Microsoft Clarity (session replay and heatmaps), and other Microsoft marketing and analytics tools. Data collected may include pages visited, actions taken (such as purchases or form submissions), and behavioral metrics. This helps improve ad targeting, conversion tracking, and user experience analysis.
cs_block_ln_tag_scripts_descr: LinkedIn conversion tracking is an analytical function powered by the LinkedIn Insight Tag. Conversion tracking gathers insights into post-click and view-through conversions of your LinkedIn ads campaigns, giving you the ability to measure the impact and ROI of your ads.
cs_block_pin_tag_scripts_desc: The Pinterest tag allows website owners to track actions people take on their website after viewing a Promoted Pin.
cs_block_yt_embedded_scripts_descr: YouTube Embedded content is used to display YouTube videos on this website. YouTube scripts can collect data about users and how they interact with the videos.
cs_block_vimeo_embedded_scripts_descr: Vimeo Embedded content is used to display Vimeo videos on this website. Vimeo scripts can collect data about users and how they interact with the videos.
cs_block_google_adsense_scripts_descr: Google AdSense allows websites to earn money by using a Google display tool on the website to host third-party ads that are relevant to their audience.
cs_block_hubspot_scripts_descr: Use HubSpot's traffic analytics tool to view website traffic data. This includes viewing traffic by source, topic cluster, device type, country, and more.
cs_block_matomo_scripts_descr: When you use the Matomo (Piwik) JavaScript Tracker Matomo will by default track the following information: User IP address (see also: IP anonymisation), Optional User ID, Date and time of the request, Title of the page being viewed (Page Title), URL of the page being viewed (Page URL), URL of the page that was viewed prior to the current page (Referrer URL), Screen resolution being used, Time in local userâ€™s timezone, Files that were clicked and downloaded (Download), Links to an outside domain that were clicked (Outlink), Pages generation time (the time it takes for webpages to be generated by the webserver and then downloaded by the user: Page speed), Location of the user: country, region, city, approximate latitude and longitude (Geolocation), Main Language of the browser being used (Accept-Language header), User Agent of the browser being used (User-Agent header).
cs_block_google_maps_scripts_descr: Google Maps is a web mapping platform and consumer application offered by Google.
cs_block_addthis_scripts_descr: AddThis is a social bookmarking service that can be integrated into a website with the use of a web widget. AddThis widget allows us to measure the amount of traffic and viral lift we get from sharing.
cs_block_sharethis_scripts_descr: ShareThis is a technology company that provides free engagement and growth tools (e.g., share buttons, follow buttons, and reaction buttons) for site owners.
cs_block_soundcloud_scripts_descr: Soundcloud embedded content is used to display Soundcloud content on this website. Soundcloud scripts can collect data about users and how they interact with the content.
cs_block_slideshare_scripts_descr: Slideshare embedded content is used to display Slideshare content on this website. Slideshare scripts can collect data about users and how they interact with the content.
cs_block_instagram_scripts_descr: Instagram Embed code allows website owners to get public Instagram photos, videos, Reel, or Guide posts embed HTML code and use it to embed the post in their websites. It can track how users interact with the embedded content.
cs_block_hotjar_scripts_descr: The Hotjar Tracking Code is used to trigger data collection when installed within your site. This code is responsible for collecting and sending the data to your Hotjar account.
cs_block_googlefonts_scripts_descr: Google Fonts is a font embedding service library. Google Fonts are stored on Google's CDN. The Google Fonts API is designed to limit the collection, storage, and use of end-user data to only what is needed to serve fonts efficiently. Use of Google Fonts API is unauthenticated. No cookies are sent by website visitors to the Google Fonts API. Requests to the Google Fonts API are made to resource-specific domains, such as fonts.googleapis.com or fonts.gstatic.com. This means your font requests are separate from and don't contain any credentials you send to google.com while using other Google services that are authenticated, such as Gmail.
cs_block_google_captcha_scripts_descr: A randomly generated sequence of letters and/or numbers that appear as a distorted image, and a text box.
cs_block_ce_scripts_descr: Conversion Exporter is a tracking tool that collects and exports conversion data from website interactions. It monitors user actions such as form submissions, purchases, downloads, and other goal completions to help analyze marketing campaign effectiveness and user behavior patterns.
cs_block_reddit_pixel_scripts_descr: Reddit Tag collects data about user interactions on your website to help measure ad performance and optimize campaigns across Reddit Ads. It enables conversion tracking and audience analytics by recording actions such as page views, clicks, add-to-cart events, and purchases. The collected data supports improved ad targeting, performance measurement, and optimization of advertising strategies based on user behavior.
